webpackJsonp([0x703cbf7050ef],{4910:function(e,t){e.exports={pathContext:{group:[{node:{fields:{title:"Volksmusik as a Product Defect",date:"10 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-10-volksmusik-as-a-product-defect/",tags:"Y2007"},html:'<p>If you are forced to listen to Volksmusik on your Caribbean cruise, <a href="http://www.margaret-marks.com/Transblawg/archives/002255.html">you might be entitled to a refund</a>, a court in Frankfurt has decided. In this case, 60 German tourists who had been promised Caribbean music were on a ship with 500 members of a Swiss folklore club. They were entitled to a 40% refund.</p>\n<p>I wonder if this could a precedent to request a partial refund of the broadcast fees we pay to the GEZ. I\'m sure we could prove that the Volksmusik programs on ARD and ZDF constitute <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cruel_and_unusual_punishment">"cruel and unusual punishment"</a>.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Could Be Winnipeg",date:"10 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-10-could-be-winnipeg/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"My Obama",date:"12 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-12-my-obama/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Could Be Winnipeg",date:"10 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-10-could-be-winnipeg/",tags:"Y2007"},html:'<p>You know the weather\'s cold when the best thing you can say about is <a href="http://accordionguy.blogware.com/blog/_archives/2007/2/9/2721696.html">"it could be worse, we could be in Winnipeg"</a>. Or when you can point out the little used fact that "-40 is where the Celsius and Fahrenheit scales meet".</p>\n<p>Considering that cities have a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heat_island">heat island</a> that raises the temperature by about 5°C, it\'s even colder than it sounds. The coldest I\'ve experienced was -31°F on a sunny day in Minneapolis. (Minnesotans often brag about the wind chill, but I\'m talking about actual temperature.)</p>\n<p>By the way, it\'s not that cold here. It\'s a balmy -2°C with 5 cm of snow that will be gone by tomorrow evening.</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Hello World, We're Here Again",date:"09 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-09-hello-world-were-here-again/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Volksmusik as a Product Defect",date:"10 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-10-volksmusik-as-a-product-defect/"}}},{node:{fields:{title:"Hello World, We're Here Again",date:"09 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-09-hello-world-were-here-again/",tags:"Y2007"},html:'<blockquote>\n  Cmon everybody do you want something real?<br />\n  Cant seem to get ahead but its no big deal<br />\n  Floating like a feather in a wide open space<br />\n  Landing in a perfect happy place\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>Today is my birthday. I turn 45 today. But instead of you wishing me happy birthday, let\'s turn the tables. I want to wish all of you all the best today. And for the coming year. And for the rest of your life. Enjoy!</p>\n<blockquote><p>\n  I hear what I wanna here living on Cloud Nine<br />\n  Jumping on a bed of flowers chasing the time<br />\n  "Oh its a hard road" says everyone I meet<br />\n  We cant trust the ground beneath our feet\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>(Lyrics: <a href="http://gogos.com/dd/music.html">La La Land by the Go-Go\'s</a>)</p>'},next:{fields:{title:"Wrong Passport",date:"07 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-07-wrong-passport/"}},previous:{fields:{title:"Could Be Winnipeg",date:"10 Feb 2007",slug:"/2007-02-10-could-be-winnipeg/"}}}],pathPrefix:"",first:!1,last:!1,index:156,pageCount:1101}}}});
